summary: Iffy-Brie anon here. The Stan Lee post was about his death though? She literally said "rip". And yeah I don't think anyone...
question: Iffy-Brie anon here. The Stan Lee post was about his death though? She literally said "rip". And yeah I don't think anyone actually bought up Monica to her but she said she's done research on her character. I don't believe she did not find out about Monica. All that talk about inclusion for WOC and she doesn't ever acknowledge Monica. It's not a death sentence to be a feminist in Hollywood anymore and her activism seems fake to some people, only serving to give her an edge. 1/2
answer: I see where you’re coming from. I get the iffyness. As a woc my eyebrows are a little raised. But it’s only one situation. My love respect and support obviously stand. Strong.

summary: the thing about the selfie; it was in no way related to stan Lee's death tho, like no "tribute" as the other anon claims, idk if...
question: the thing about the selfie; it was in no way related to stan Lee's death tho, like no "tribute" as the other anon claims, idk if she knew about his death when she posted it, it's just the same day, but it could have been before she found out... as for acknowledging Monica as the first captain marvel, idk if it was ever brought up to her directly. not denying monica was the first one to wear the name, but shes more known as photon, which I guess is where her story goes in the next movies,,,
answer:
Got it, got it. Of course. At the same time we can’t expect these people to be perfect and unproblematic all the time. They aren’t always going to make everyone happy as much as they may want to. They’re human beings.


Right. I think if Monica was the ‘first’ Captain Marvel, I don’t see why Brie wouldn’t have mentioned if she knew about it… these actors who should know a lot about Marvel really don’t. You’d be surprised

summary: i know this makes no sense because i am a 27 year old black woman from a tiny caribbean island who's in a constant state of...
